BNP Paribas Chairman Pebereau Will Retire; Bonnafe Becomes CEO

-- B y   F a b i o   B e n e d e t t i - V a l e n t i n i
-- 
2011-05-11T14:01:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/bonnafe-named-ceo-of-bnp-prot-to-be-chairman-as-pebereau-plans-to-retire.html
BNP Paribas (BNP)  SA Chairman Michel Pebereau, who masterminded the creation of  Europe â€™s largest
lender by assets out of a French state-owned bank, said he will
retire by the end of the year.  Pebereau, 69, made the announcement in a prepared speech to
be delivered to shareholders gathered in Paris today for their
annual general meeting. He will be succeeded as chairman by
Baudouin Prot, currently chief executive officer, on Dec. 1.
Jean-Laurent Bonnafe, chief operating officer since 2008, will
become CEO, Pebereau said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
